item.description:
@xx_qwertyuiop_xx wrote:

[quote=“noobie22, post:10, topic:275845”][quote author=`Rich link=topic=364370.msg2765922#msg2765922 date=1240792506]
He gave you an example…
[/quote]

Thank you.

Noobspure50, we do not spoon-feed here.

@Noobspure

The variable cannot return a value(number) from a void whos return is false

In noob language-

The number cannot be identified when the return statement is false.

@Jc

Good point. Take out the variable part.[/quote]
A value is not necessarily a number…
A method whose return type is void cannot return a value, so get rid of the return false.

Oh, and here’s the home command

if (command.startsWith("home")) {
    if (isInWilderness) {
        sM("You cannot teleport while fighting or while in the wild!");
    } else {
        toX = 3087;
        toY = 3500;
        sM("Welcome home.");
    }
}
